events.name: New England Patriots at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: — Cam Akers rushed for 171 yards in a breakout performance, Kenny Young returned an interception 79 yards for a touchdown and the Los Angeles Rams clinched their fourth straight winning season with a 24-3 victory over the New England Patriots on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Akers runs wild, Newton benched as Rams rout Patriots 24-3

headlines.description: — Mitchell Trubisky threw three touchdown passes to outplay Deshaun Watson in their first meeting since they entered the NFL, and the Chicago Bears snapped a six-game losing streak with a 36-7 victory over the Houston Texans on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trubisky outplays Watson, Bears stop skid, beat Texans 36-7

headlines.description: — Andy Dalton was good enough in his return to Cincinnati, tossing two touchdown passes and helping lead the Dallas Cowboys to a 30-7 win over the Bengals on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dalton returns to Cincy, leads Cowboys over Bengals 30-7

events.name: Kansas City Chiefs at Miami Dolphins

headlines.description: — Patrick Mahomes and the Kansas City Chiefs overcame a 30-yard sack, four turnovers and a 10-point deficit Sunday to clinch their fifth consecutive AFC West title by beating Miami 33-27 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes, Chiefs clinch AFC West with 33-27 win over Dolphins

events.name: Arizona Cardinals at New York Giants

headlines.description: — Haason Reddick had a franchise-record five sacks and three forced fumbles as the Arizona Cardinals spoiled the return of Giants quarterback Daniel Jones and moved back into an NFC playoff spot with a 26-7 victory over New York on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray throws TD, Cards end 3-game skid, beat red-hot Giants

events.name: Minnesota Vikings at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: — Tom Brady threw for 196 yards and two touchdowns on Sunday, helping the Tampa Bay Buccaneers bolster their playoff hopes with a 26-14 victory over the Minnesota Vikings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brady throws for 2 TDs, Buccaneers wear down Vikings 26-14

headlines.description: — Drew Lock threw for 280 yards and a career-high four touchdowns, Diontae Spencer returned a punt 83 yards for his first career score and the Denver Broncos held on to beat the Carolina Panthers 32-27 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lock throws career-high 4 TDs, Broncos top Panthers 32-27

headlines.description: — Derrick Henry ran for 215 yards and two touchdowns, his best performance in five trips to his hometown area, and the Tennessee Titans dominated Jacksonville 31-10 on Sunday and handed the Jaguars a 12th consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henry runs wild, Titans hand Jags 12th straight loss, 31-10

events.name: Indianapolis Colts at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: — T.Y. Hilton caught two touchdown passes from Philip Rivers, Jonathan Taylor rushed for a career-best 150 yards and two scores, and the Indianapolis Colts solidified their spot in the AFC playoff race with a 44-27 victory over the Las Vegas Raiders...
headlines.shortLinkText: Hilton, Taylor lead Colts' 44-27 rout of fading Raiders

events.name: New York Jets at Seattle Seahawks

headlines.description: — Russell Wilson threw four more touchdowns passes to give him a new career-high with 36 for the season before finally resting in the fourth quarter, leading the Seattle Seahawks to a 40-3 rout of the New York Jets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson throws 4 more TDs, Seahawks rout winless Jets 40-3

events.name: Green Bay Packers at Detroit Lions

headlines.description: — Aaron Rodgers ran for a tiebreaking score in the third quarter and threw three touchdown passes and the Green Bay Packers beat the Detroit Lions 31-24 Sunday and clinched the NFC North...
headlines.shortLinkText: Rodgers-led Packers beat Lions 31-24, clinch NFC North title

events.name: New Orleans Saints at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: — Jalen Hurts gave the Philadelphia Eagles more than just a spark. He helped deliver a victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Hurts helps Eagles beat Saints 24-21

events.name: Atlanta Falcons at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: — Michael Badgley hit a 43-yard field goal as time expired and the Los Angeles Chargers rallied for a 20-17 victory over the Atlanta Falcons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Badgley's FG on final play propels Chargers past Falcons

headlines.description: — Rookies Chase Young and Kamren Curl scored defensive touchdowns and Washington grabbed sole possession of first place in the NFC East after a gritty 23-15 win over the San Francisco 49ers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington leads NFC East after gritty 23-15 win over 49ers

headlines.description: — Josh Allen threw two touchdown passes and safety Taron Johnson returned an interception 51 yards for a score in the Buffalo Bills' 26-15 win over the Pittsburgh Steelers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bills improve to 10-3 with 26-15 win over sloppy Steelers

headlines.description: — Lamar Jackson emerged from the locker room, saved the game and maybe Baltimore's season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson returns to save Ravens with 47-42 win over Browns
